I'm more concerned with not breaking *existing* code (using magic method names):

```python
from traitlets import *

class Foo(HasTraits):

    bar = Int()

    @observe('bar')
    def _bar_changed(self, change):
        print('base')

class Baz(Foo):

    def _bar_changed(self, name, old, new):
        print('derived')
        super()._bar_changed(name, old, new)

b = Baz()
b.bar = 5
```

Having to register `@observe('bar')` on subclasses in order for override to work (it already does) doesn't seem too problematic to me (though frankly, I don't find the new API to be clearer or simpler than the old, since it requires more code to use).

