In thrift_sasl, this is the definition of TSaslClientTransport:
```
class TSaslClientTransport(TTransportBase, CReadableTransport):
    ...
```

And in thrift, this is the definition of TTransportBase:
```
class TTransportBase(object):
    """Base class for Thrift transport layer."""

    def isOpen(self):
        pass

    def open(self):
        pass

    def close(self):
        pass

    def read(self, sz):
        pass

    def readAll(self, sz):
        buff = b''
        have = 0
        while (have < sz):
            chunk = self.read(sz - have)
            have += len(chunk)
            buff += chunk

            if len(chunk) == 0:
                raise EOFError()

        return buff

    def write(self, buf):
        pass

    def flush(self):
        pass
```

So `readAll` should be defined. Can you double check what's in your packages? Maybe try virtualenv instead of anaconda. You can also compare with the packages installed in the Travis build log at https://travis-ci.org/dropbox/PyHive/jobs/268808892.

