```
class MobileLoader(django.template.loaders.filesystem.Loader):
    """
    This template loader replaces .html with .m.html and tries to load that
    """
    is_usable = True

    def load_template(self, template_name, template_dirs=None):
        request = get_current_request()
        if not request:
            return super(MobileLoader, self).load_template(template_name, template_dirs)
        if hasattr(request, 'is_mobile') and request.is_mobile and template_name.endswith('.html') and not template_name.endswith('.m.html'):
            template_name = template_name[:-5] + '.m.html'
        return super(MobileLoader, self).load_template(template_name, template_dirs)

```

get_current_request is using the thread local storage for storing a reference to the current request.

