`data-fa-processed` has been replaced with `data-fa-i2svg`. This attribute has existed as a way for the Font Awesome engine to detect and work with `<svg>` icons that have been processed with `fontawesome.dom.i2svg()`.

It was renamed to make the intent more clear and fix an existing bug. With 5.0.6 icons that are created with `fontawesome.icon` will not contain this attribute (this previously caused an issue with components like react-fontawesome and vue-fontawesome.)

