@DeNeutoy I think the current behavior is actually correct.

The cache is in memory and only works for the duration of the process--it does not use the database.  It will be clean slate once you update a model and restart the process.

The permalinks do use the database and they always return the same information that you saw previously.  I think it would be confusing if the response changed when our models improved.

